 the union government is exercising the power given  to  it  under  article  262  of  the  constitution    now the  salient  feature  of  the proposed  system  is  that  there  will  be  a  permanent  tribunal  instead  of  different tribunals  comprising  a  chairman  deputy  chairman  and  maximum  six  members  their  maximum  age  limit  will  be  70  years    a  committee  would  be  constituted before referring any water dispute to the tribunal and the tribunal will dispose such disputes within a maximum time span of four to five years the bill was introduced   